# Implementation

parameters:
  tasks: all from sp.task
  output_format:
    - Step-by-step instructions per task
    - Include code (ROS 2, Gazebo, Isaac, Python)
    - Hardware setup (Jetson, RealSense, mic)
    - Cloud vs Edge deployment
    - Troubleshooting tips
notes:
  - Each task: Objective, Inputs, Output, Commands, Testing, Optional enhancements
  - Examples: 
      - ROS2: ros2 run <pkg> <node>, ros2 topic list
      - Gazebo: gazebo <world>.world, spawn_entity.py -entity <robot>
      - Isaac: python3 launch_simulation.py --robot <robot>, vslam_launch.py
  - Hardware: flash Jetson, calibrate RealSense, test mic
  - Troubleshooting: check ros2 doctor, reduce sim graphics, recalibrateÂ VSLAM

  

Pipeline:
- Data Ingestion: Load and process chapters
- Text Chunking: 500-700 token chunks with overlap
- Embeddings: Sentence-transformers model

Backend:
- FastAPI: Async endpoints, CORS, validation
- RAG: Similarity search, response generation
- Vector DB: Qdrant integration, filtering

Frontend:
- Chat: Real-time comm, history, typing indicators
- Search: Semantic, context-aware queries

Deployment:
- Production: Env configs, cloud integration
- Performance: Caching, async processing

QA:
- Testing: Unit, integration, end-to-end
- Validation: Accuracy, UX, security